---
// Founding section index — The Eighth Anchor Institute founding booklet (v4).
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Founding Proposal — The Eighth Anchor Institute"
  description="The founding proposal for The Eighth Anchor Institute: an institution that brings the empirical record of America's school trust lands into the design of the AI-era's forever-trusts, governed by a human board, led by a human chief executive, and powered by an AI Engine Room under human direction."
  path="/founding/"
  ogTitle="Founding Proposal — The Eighth Anchor Institute"
  ogDescription="An institute governed by a human board, led by a human chief executive, and powered by an AI Engine Room that runs production under human direction and accountability."
>
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="bg-eai-navy text-eai-parchment">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-5 py-20 md:py-24">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-4">
        Founding Proposal
      </p>
      <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-eai-bone leading-tight">
        The Eighth Anchor Institute
      </h1>
      <p class="font-serif italic text-eai-parchment/85 text-xl mt-3">
        An institute for intergenerational trust design.
      </p>
      <div class="prose prose-invert max-w-none mt-8 text-eai-parchment/90 leading-relaxed">
        <p class="italic text-eai-parchment/85 text-lg">
          An institute that brings the empirical record of America's school trust
          lands into the design of the AI-era's forever-trusts. Governed by a human
          board, led by a human chief executive, and powered by an AI "Engine Room"
          that runs the production line under human direction and accountability.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Cover image -->
  <section class="bg-eai-parchment border-b border-eai-blueprint/20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-5 py-12 md:py-16">
      <img
        src="/images/founding/cover.png"
        alt="The Eighth Anchor Institute — founding booklet cover"
        class="w-full max-w-md mx-auto shadow-lg border border-eai-blueprint/20"
        loading="eager"
      />
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Overview -->
  <section class="bg-eai-bone">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-5 py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-3">
        Overview
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-eai-navy mb-8">The proposition</h2>
      <article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none text-eai-navy/90 leading-relaxed font-serif">
        <p>
          Humanity has begun a transfer that will define the next several centuries —
          power, skills, legacy, and capital moving from biological intelligence to
          artificial intelligence. The institutions being chartered to hold that
          transfer — sovereign AI funds, perpetual climate endowments, longevity
          escrows, compute-reserve trusts — are being designed right now, on horizons
          of centuries, by people working without a body of empirical evidence on what
          actually happens to a fiduciary structure that must hold its purpose across
          many human generations.
        </p>
        <p>
          America's school trust lands are the best-documented, longest-running public
          fiduciary record we have for exactly that problem: two centuries of recorded
          experience with the same legal form, across twenty separately governed
          jurisdictions, with the same beneficiary class written into the founding
          instruments. The record shows two compounding failure modes — gradual drift
          and sudden directed seizure — and it also shows the defenses that hold. The
          Eighth Anchor Institute exists to carry that record to the architects of the
          new forever-trusts, in language they read and on the timeline their work is
          running on.
        </p>
        <p>
          The Institute's production model is deliberately different where it can afford
          to be, and conventional exactly where it counts. A human board holds the
          Institute. A human chief executive leads it. An AI "Engine Room" runs the
          production line — research, drafting, the publication cadence, the Library —
          under human direction and accountability. Every fiduciary and legal duty
          rests with a named human. The unusual part is the engine, not the chain of
          accountability — and the engine is documented in public.
        </p>
        <p class="text-eai-blueprint italic">
          The four sections that follow give the evidence to evaluate the proposition:
          the thesis underneath the work, the programs that carry it out, the operating
          model that makes it possible at this scale, and the honest list of what could
          go wrong.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Section nav cards -->
  <section class="bg-eai-parchment border-t border-eai-blueprint/20">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-5 py-16 md:py-20">
      <p class="font-mono text-[11px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-3">
        The four sections
      </p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl text-eai-navy mb-8">Read in order</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        <a href="/founding/vision/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 1</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Vision</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            The thesis. Why the best long-running public fiduciary record we have needs
            to reach the people designing the AI-era's forever-trusts, and why no one has
            built the bridge yet.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/founding/programs/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 2</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Programs and Direction</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            The six things the Institute does — anchored by the Reference Library and the
            Knowledge Stack beneath it — the two books at its core, and the first-year push
            to bring four sites and two books online at speed.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/founding/operations/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 3</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Operations and Organization</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            The structure: a human board, a human chief executive, and an AI Engine Room
            that runs production under human direction — with a disclosure architecture
            that makes the whole machine inspectable.
          </p>
        </a>
        <a href="/founding/risks/" class="block bg-eai-bone border border-eai-blueprint/30 p-6 hover:border-eai-gold transition-colors">
          <p class="font-mono text-[10px] tracking-[0.22em] uppercase text-eai-gold mb-2">Section 4</p>
          <h3 class="font-serif text-2xl text-eai-navy mb-2">Risks</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-eai-navy/75 leading-relaxed">
            The honest failure modes — reputational risk on the form, the operations seam,
            and Margaret Bird's bandwidth — and how each one is handled.
          </p>
        </a>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-10 flex justify-end">
        <a href="/founding/vision/" class="font-serif text-eai-navy hover:text-eai-gold">
          Start with Section 1: Vision &rarr;
        </a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
